<!DOCTYPE assessment PUBLIC "-//Carnegie Mellon University//DTD Inline Assessment MathML 1.4//EN" "http://oli.cmu.edu/dtd/oli_inline_assessment_mathml_1_4.dtd"><assessment xmlns:cmd="http://oli.web.cmu.edu/content/metadata/2.1/" id="newdfdbb13a48d349b0b2f2e551e2f8d97d"><title>New Formative Assessment</title><page id="e81e0da1eaf94b2c976780ae739472b7"><title>Page 1</title><question id="newdfdbb13a48d349b0b2f2e551e2f8d97d_1a"><body><p id="b0c8878007f843ebbae528ebe023cbf8">You are exploring a dataset and have examined that the symmetry and found that your skewness coefficient is between -0.5 and 0.5, this means that:</p></body><multiple_choice shuffle="false" select="single" id="ans" labels="false"><choice value="yes">Your data is symmetrical.</choice><choice value="no">Your data is moderately skewed. </choice><choice value="f15098a5eb604d81aef46585b7cf2060">Your data is highly skewed.</choice></multiple_choice><part id="fd56d614f8f7471088e85e966a002ef2"><response match="yes" score="1"><feedback><p id="fa3b0c1a22eb413c911baa0b0a42854c">Correct: if you have found skewness to be between -0.5 and 0.5, you can ascertain that your data is symmetrical. </p></feedback></response><response match="no" score="0"><feedback><p id="b02fe0c33e304e32b2ce85c86ed1db23">Incorrect: If skewness is between -1 and -0.5 or 0.5 and 1, then your data is moderately skewed. </p></feedback></response><response match="f15098a5eb604d81aef46585b7cf2060" score="0"><feedback><p id="c1fa018e1a0b4d45a8356732c038e47f">Incorrect:  If skewness is &lt; -1 or &gt; 1, your data is highly skewed.</p></feedback></response></part></question><question id="eadef830040c4d769c1560fcb9289497"><body><p id="fb845313cc4343cc96df9a61fda44c14">Which pair below reflects the central value of a variable:</p></body><multiple_choice shuffle="true" select="single" id="aa785597df7e4bd2b7f9751119b60f27" labels="false"><choice value="e36d7c795f024e5a8ecfa676b55aa743">Mean and Median.</choice><choice value="b7fee8db60314fc6af3ee8b8d13a9696">Variance and Sample Standard Deviation.</choice><choice value="d35fae054c9f490bac5ce7ce0eb9b3f7">Covariance and Correlation.</choice></multiple_choice><part id="fe87146a5b7e474d9a83aa2cdbf7d072"><response match="e36d7c795f024e5a8ecfa676b55aa743" score="1"><feedback><p id="ea0bedc1c1564fb1a10685b57952af0b">Correct: These are measures of central tendency!</p></feedback></response><response match="b7fee8db60314fc6af3ee8b8d13a9696" score="0"><feedback><p id="b0553e1833244c018a0e996aa200230d">Incorrect: These are measures of dispersion of the data.</p></feedback></response><response match="d35fae054c9f490bac5ce7ce0eb9b3f7" score="0"><feedback><p id="bc598ef15f6b4a1b92baf32f0065a83a">Incorrect: These are measures of associations between variables in your dataset.</p></feedback></response></part></question><question id="e76f920ca6ed436ca1ca068fd24cbb77"><body><p id="d9bc09fc157e4b2690e5e7035a783bab">This type of chart displays a numerical variable as a series of data points connected by a line.</p></body><multiple_choice shuffle="true" select="single" id="b4822fac4f744101bd9c1bccaa83b143" labels="false"><choice value="c61ef3ab3092455c919f745621b366fb">A line chart.</choice><choice value="d15518579420467287aa32da23af56d8">A bar chart.</choice><choice value="fe17184853a541819e9c3f5e57080d9a">A histogram.</choice></multiple_choice><part id="e5f3f0976dae4ff6ad71d51fe01e75e0"><response match="c61ef3ab3092455c919f745621b366fb" score="1"><feedback><p id="ac80948ce0ae40c0ab22fe5e821f3fc0">Correct: A line chart plots trends as well.</p></feedback></response><response match="d15518579420467287aa32da23af56d8" score="0"><feedback><p id="e057dbdd82bd44b9a1c0f84a825c5432">Incorrect: Bar charts show a frequency distribution.</p></feedback></response><response match="fe17184853a541819e9c3f5e57080d9a" score="0"><feedback><p id="eb47a206305149f99a9696731aca53e2">Incorrect: This chart is used to chart categorical variables.</p></feedback></response></part></question></page></assessment>
